President Donald J. Trump met with Prime Minister Theresa May of the United Kingdom to discuss various topics. They talked about ending Iran's destabilizing influence in Syria and Iraq, as well as reviewing next steps on the Iran nuclear deal. President Trump asked the UK to increase pressure on North Korea to denuclearize. They also discussed improving joint efforts on counterterrorism, particularly addressing the use of the Internet by terrorists. Prime Minister May updated President Trump on the status of the Brexit negotiations.